<?xml version="1.1" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<databaseChangeLog
        xmlns="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog"
        xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
        xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog
        http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog/dbchangelog-latest.xsd">

    <!--
        #1198 Unified Integration Framework — consolidated branch-scoped changelog.

        This single file replaces twelve incremental changesets that accreted across
        the long #1198 audit loop. The branch is the unit of release: collapsing the
        history into one timestamped file with each table declared in its FINAL shape
        is cheaper to review and removes the obsolete two-phase (backfill → cutover)
        plumbing the iteration carried.

        Logical contents:

          1.  Connection aggregate + audit + partial-unique for NULL instance_key.
          2.  integration_webhook_subscription per-subscription signing-secret sidecar.
          3.  feedback_post cross-vendor edit-in-place tracking.
          4.  agent_job classification columns (integration_kind, subject_class)
              + (kind, subject, created_at) index.
          5.  practice capability gating (required_capabilities, required_aspects,
              required_family).
          6.  slack_channel + slack_message persistence (ToS-compliant, see
              SlackMessage javadoc).
          7.  outline_collection + outline_document persistence.
          8.  shedlock distributed-lock table (JdbcTemplateLockProvider schema).
          9.  oauth_state_nonce (with code_verifier PKCE column declared from the
              start) — single-use nonce + RFC 7636 S256 verifier storage.
         10.  Unconditional drop of the eleven legacy Workspace columns superseded
              by the Connection registry. account_login is intentionally KEPT —
              40+ join sites depend on it as a denormalised org/group lookup column.

         Note: the hephaestus_user + integration_identity tables that appeared in
         earlier revisions of this changelog were removed before merge — the
         Java entities, repositories, and JpaUserDirectory wiring were never
         consumed in production. See ADR 0011 (now historical) + the
         "unified-identity-keycloak-as-truth" ADR (0016) for the model we
         actually ship: SCM User is authoritative, keycloak_subject is the
         persisted stable join key.

        Decision — no data backfill: the branch ships as a clean migration. The
        interim WorkspaceConnectionBackfillChange customChange that moved data
        from the legacy columns into Connection rows was retired together with
        the columns it sourced from.

        Preconditions strategy — every changeset uses onFail="MARK_RAN" so
        re-applying against a partially-migrated environment (e.g. someone manually
        applied a subset of the old 12 files locally) stays forward-only safe. The
        DROP COLUMN changesets carry preconditions in the same belt-and-braces
        style; they no-op on a fresh DB where the column was never created, and
        apply on an existing DB where the column is still present.

        OPERATOR WARNING — DATA-LOSS GUARD INTENTIONALLY OMITTED on the DROP COLUMN
        block (section 11 below):
          * ON FRESH DB: legacy Workspace columns are empty by construction; the
            drops are no-ops on column-content. Safe.
          * ON IN-FLIGHT DB carrying real student-facing data: the eleven dropped
            columns (installation_id, personal_access_token, git_provider_mode,
            slack_token, slack_signing_secret, gitlab_group_id, gitlab_webhook_id,
            server_url, leaderboard_notification_team,
            leaderboard_notification_channel_id, installation_linked_at) WILL be
            destroyed without warning. Their successor — rows in the {@code
            connection} table — must be backfilled OUT-OF-BAND BEFORE this
            migration runs. The interim WorkspaceConnectionBackfillChange
            customChange that previously performed the backfill in-Liquibase
            was retired with the legacy columns. Operators upgrading a live
            environment must replicate that logic externally (script or admin
            task) and verify the connection table is populated before applying
            this changelog.
    -->

    <!-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         1. Connection aggregate + audit + format-version + NULL-collision guard.
         ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->

    <changeSet author="hephaestus-1198" id="1779790459343-1">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN" onFailMessage="connection table already present">
            <not><tableExists tableName="connection"/></not>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>Connection aggregate — multi-instance natural key (workspace_id, kind, instance_key).</comment>
        <createTable tableName="connection">
            <column name="id" type="bigserial">
                <constraints primaryKey="true" primaryKeyName="pk_connection" nullable="false"/>
            </column>
            <column name="workspace_id" type="bigint">
                <constraints nullable="false" referencedTableName="workspace" referencedColumnNames="id"
                             foreignKeyName="fk_connection_workspace"/>
            </column>
            <column name="kind" type="varchar(48)">
                <constraints nullable="false"/>
            </column>
            <!-- Nullable from the start — pre-bind OAuth slots carry NULL until the
                 vendor returns the instance handle. NULL-collision protection lives
                 on the partial unique index uq_connection_pending below. -->
            <column name="instance_key" type="varchar(128)"/>
            <column name="display_name" type="varchar(256)"/>
            <column name="state" type="varchar(32)" defaultValue="PENDING">
                <constraints nullable="false"/>
            </column>
            <column name="state_reason" type="varchar(512)"/>
            <column name="config" type="jsonb" defaultValueComputed="'{}'::jsonb">
                <constraints nullable="false"/>
            </column>
            <column name="credentials_encrypted" type="bytea"/>
            <column name="credentials_alg" type="varchar(64)"/>
            <column name="created_at" type="timestamp with time zone" defaultValueComputed="NOW()">
                <constraints nullable="false"/>
            </column>
            <column name="updated_at" type="timestamp with time zone" defaultValueComputed="NOW()">
                <constraints nullable="false"/>
            </column>
            <column name="last_activity_at" type="timestamp with time zone"/>
            <column name="version" type="bigint" defaultValueNumeric="0">
                <constraints nullable="false"/>
            </column>
        </createTable>
        <addUniqueConstraint tableName="connection"
                             columnNames="workspace_id, kind, instance_key"
                             constraintName="uq_connection"/>
        <sql>
            ALTER TABLE connection ADD CONSTRAINT ck_connection_kind
                CHECK (kind IN ('GITHUB','GITLAB','SLACK','OUTLINE'));
            ALTER TABLE connection ADD CONSTRAINT ck_connection_state
                CHECK (state IN ('PENDING','ACTIVE','SUSPENDED','UNINSTALLED'));
        </sql>
        <createIndex tableName="connection" indexName="ix_connection_active">
            <column name="workspace_id"/>
            <column name="kind"/>
        </createIndex>
        <rollback>
            <dropTable tableName="connection"/>
        </rollback>
    </changeSet>

    <changeSet author="hephaestus-1198" id="1779790459343-2">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN" onFailMessage="uq_connection_pending partial index already present">
            <not><indexExists indexName="uq_connection_pending"/></not>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>
            Partial unique over (workspace_id, kind) WHERE instance_key IS NULL — closes
            the NULL-collision gap left by the base uq_connection (PostgreSQL treats
            NULL as distinct in standard unique constraints, so a workspace could
            otherwise install the same vendor twice in the pre-bind state).
        </comment>
        <sql>
            CREATE UNIQUE INDEX uq_connection_pending
                ON connection (workspace_id, kind)
                WHERE instance_key IS NULL;
        </sql>
        <rollback>
            <sql>DROP INDEX IF EXISTS uq_connection_pending;</sql>
        </rollback>
    </changeSet>

    <changeSet author="hephaestus-1198" id="1779790459343-3">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN" onFailMessage="connection_audit already present">
            <not><tableExists tableName="connection_audit"/></not>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>Connection audit — append-only with correlation-id idempotency on webhook replay.</comment>
        <createTable tableName="connection_audit">
            <column name="id" type="bigserial">
                <constraints primaryKey="true" primaryKeyName="pk_connection_audit" nullable="false"/>
            </column>
            <column name="connection_id" type="bigint">
                <constraints nullable="false" referencedTableName="connection" referencedColumnNames="id"
                             foreignKeyName="fk_connection_audit_connection"/>
            </column>
            <column name="event_type" type="varchar(48)">
                <constraints nullable="false"/>
            </column>
            <column name="from_state" type="varchar(32)"/>
            <column name="to_state" type="varchar(32)"/>
            <column name="actor_kind" type="varchar(32)">
                <constraints nullable="false"/>
            </column>
            <column name="actor_ref" type="varchar(256)"/>
            <column name="correlation_id" type="varchar(64)"/>
            <column name="detail" type="jsonb"/>
            <column name="occurred_at" type="timestamp with time zone" defaultValueComputed="NOW()">
                <constraints nullable="false"/>
            </column>
        </createTable>
        <addUniqueConstraint tableName="connection_audit"
                             columnNames="connection_id, event_type, correlation_id"
                             constraintName="uq_connection_audit_idempotency"/>
        <createIndex tableName="connection_audit" indexName="ix_connection_audit_lookup">
            <column name="connection_id"/>
            <column name="occurred_at" descending="true"/>
        </createIndex>
        <rollback>
            <dropTable tableName="connection_audit"/>
        </rollback>
    </changeSet>

    <!-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         2. integration_webhook_subscription per-subscription secret sidecar.
         ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->

    <changeSet author="hephaestus-1198" id="1779790459343-5">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN" onFailMessage="integration_webhook_subscription already present">
